  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project has three main objectives. The first will be to conduct research and produce 2 investigative reports on the food land climate crisis nexus. Second, GRAIN will maintain and improve their trilingual website (www.grain.org), which has over 1 million visitors per year. They will launch a new scrolling website that explains how the global food system and climate change are linked. Finally, funds from this grant will enable GRAIN to participate in 2 partner meetings in Latin America, 2 partner meetings in Africa and 1 partner meeting in Asia. The purpose of these meetings will be to raise awareness about the link between the global food system and climate change, to build the capacity of local groups to deal with the corporate push for industrial agriculture, and to provide education about achieving food sovereignty.</narrative>
  </description>
